# Vendored upstream inkjs tests live under src/inkjs/tests/ as
# reference material only — nothing in sparkdown's build or test
# harness imports from there, and our vitest config explicitly excludes
# `src/inkjs/tests/**`. The directory is gitignored entirely; if you
# need a fresh upstream snapshot to cross-check behavior, follow the
# re-vendor instructions in `src/inkjs/README.md`. The inkjs MIT license
# at `src/inkjs/LICENSE` covers the engine fork and the (untracked)
# tests directory alike.
src/inkjs/tests

# Vendored upstream Luau conformance tests are COMMITTED. Unlike the
# inkjs tests (which are reference-only), our conformance runner
# (`UpstreamConformance.test.ts`) reads from `upstream/conformance/`
# verbatim at every test run — so the files are load-bearing, not
# just reference material. Committing them keeps tests deterministic
# across machines and CI, and makes re-vendoring a reviewable commit
# rather than an environment quirk. See `upstream/VENDORING.md` for
# the re-vendor procedure.
